libapache-mod-ssl (2.8.12-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Reordered libapache-mod-ssl package maintainer scripts. They do
    not touch httpd.conf anymore, wherever it is (closes: #151687).
  * Rules to remove hash symlinks in ssl.* directories are now more
    strict (closes: #168103).
  * Modified mkcert.sh to signal an error if any of the Snake Oil CA
    misses. If _all_ the Snake Oil CA files of a given type (RSA or DSA)
    miss, mod-ssl-makecert will restore them (closes: #150302).
  * Updated Snake Oil certificates (closes: #152245).
  * libapache-mod-ssl now suggests ca-certificates.
  * Switched to debhelper package building suite.

 -- Domenico Andreoli <cavok@debian.org>  Wed,  5 Mar 2003 21:28:55 +0100

libapache-mod-ssl (2.8.12-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New maintainer.
  * New upstream release (closes: #150643, #155761, #165941).
  * Moved to main archive (closes: #142220).
  * Improved mod-ssl-makecert consistency (closes: #164147).
  * mod-ssl-makecert now prints a error message if invalid certificate
    type is entered (closes: #158996).
  * User manual is registered using doc-base, as required (closes: #132342).
  * libapache-mod-ssl-doc/README.Debian ceased to suggest a (sometimes)
    broken place for Listen directives (closes: #147118).
  * Modified sample configuration files in order to improve readability
    and usability (closes: #166881).

